      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMOKIN' BILLY (8) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 4.5 lengths at Shepparton in a handy 25.17 beating Reckless. Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Expected to go well again. KENZIE KID (1) placed two back in a Grade 5 at Sale then not far away from a tricky draw last time when fifth (26.23) at this track. This looks easier and expected to improve sharply. DR. FANATICAL (2) goes very well here including two wins. Missed the frame latest (29.50) when sixth over 510m at Sale in a Grade 4/5. With even luck and a clean start can sneak into the finish. DR. HOPPER (3) cannot be written off despite a miss here at his latest outing.",
